# 19. 空飛ぶショーステージ！？

Emu: Mikuuu!
Miku: Emuuu!
Emu & Miku: Long time no see!
KAITO: Hi, everyone! It's been a while! How have your Wonder Stage performances been going?
Tsukasa: They've been a smash hit, of course! With a star such as myself on the team, you hardly need to ask!
Nene: We came to say thank you to the two of you. Thanks for all your help.
Tsukasa: Hey! Stop stealing my lines!
Nene: You always needlessly drag things out. I was simply getting to the point.
Tsukasa: Why, you...
Rui: We really do owe you quite a lot. Please accept my thanks as well.
KAITO: You're welcome. I'm just happy we could be of assistance to you and your shows.
Tsukasa: Ahem! That actually brings us to our reason for coming today. Would you let us watch your show?
KAITO: Our show? Of course. But why the sudden request?
Tsukasa: We were discussing what to do for our next big performance, but everyone had such different opinions.
Tsukasa: We thought it'd be best to come and see what kinds of shows you perform and how you integrate everyone's ideas.
KAITO: Oh, so that's why you've come.
Tsukasa: Trying to incorporate so many opinions is harder than I thought it would be. It's even worse when everyone always suggests utterly insane ideas in opposition to my own...
KAITO: Hehe. That's what happens when you have so many people working together.
KAITO: However, that is also what leads to new ideas.
KAITO: Accepting everyone's differing talents and opinions is a great way to come up with wonderful show ideas.
Tsukasa: I see. I suppose that makes sense.
Miku: Oh! I know!
KAITO: Whoa! You startled me! What's wrong?
Miku: Since everyone is here, let's use our new attraction☆
Emu: New attraction?
Miku: Over there! It's a flying train!
Emu: A flying train?!
Emu: W-W-Wow!!! It's really flying! Woohoo☆
Nene: I'll just make sure Robo-Nene is strapped in tight. There.
Nene: So how exactly does this thing fly, anyway?
Rui: The power source must be in the engine room. Ah, I see. I'm going to have to come back and take a closer look at this later.
Tsukasa: Wh-What kind of show are you going to do up here?!
Miku: Ahem! Welcome, ladies and gentlemen! Please join me today on a journey through the skies! Is everyone ready?!
Nene: Oh, a kind of participatory performance? This could be fun.
KAITO: Please keep your hands and feet inside the train! The wind is quite strong and we wouldn't want anyone falling out!
Emu: Okay! Wh-Whoa!
Miku: Oh! Emu!
Nene: Emu! Miku! Th-They both went out the window...
Tsukasa: Wha?! Did they fall?!
Tsukasa: Oh, good. They managed to grab onto the door handle.
Emu: Eek! It's so high! Oh, look! You can see the stage from up here♪
Miku: Oh, you're right! It looks so small☆
Tsukasa: Th-This is no time to be enjoying the scenery! Grab hold!
KAITO: Tsukasa, give me your hand! Rui, you too!
Rui: Sure. Nene, there's a tow cable installed in Robo-Nene. Could you tie it around my waist and help pull us up?
Nene: You even installed a cable? Hey, aren't you a little calm considering the situation we're in?
Tsukasa: I-I thought I was a goner...
Emu: That was so much fun! Thanks for saving me, everyone! You were all superstars☆
KAITO: Haha... You're welcome.
KAITO: Sorry you weren't able to see our show after all, Tsukasa.
Tsukasa: Oh, well. I guess it wasn't a complete loss.
KAITO: It wasn't?
Tsukasa: Emu is always pulling one crazy stunt after another. But looking at it from another perspective, that just means she's able to come up with ideas I would never think of.
Tsukasa: Rui is always taking an interest in one thing or another and turning ideas into something tangible. And Nene's ability to keep calm is always helpful.
Tsukasa: This made me realize that together, we'll be able to come up with some fantastic shows for sure.
Tsukasa: Of course, that wouldn't be possible without the great, shining star that is me to bring it all together!
KAITO: (Ever since re-discovering his true feelings, Tsukasa has started acting more and more like a troupe leader.)
KAITO: Hehe. I'm glad we could be of help.
KAITO: I hope you'll all come back again, Tsukasa. We'll be sure to put on an even better show next time!
